\begin{abstract}
%% Text of abstract
As international initiatives such as the Carbon Offsetting and Reduction Scheme for International Aviation (CORSIA) have set goals for the complete decarbonization of international aviation in this century, sustainable aviation fuel (SAF) research has increased substantially, in the past decade the average yearly growth rate reached \Sexpr{S_2012_2022$AnnualGrowthRate}\%, in \Sexpr{S$AnnualProduction$`Year   `[[25]]} alone \Sexpr{S$AnnualProduction$Articles[[25]]} documents were published. This paper aims to provide an overview on SAF research to point one to the field foundations and, possibly, the future of it. Data from de Web of Science database was collected and analysed; the most important papers, cooperation networks, textual analysis, productivity and trends are provided. The most productive countries are in the global north, lead by the United States and China.
\end{abstract}

