The two central countries on the global collaboration network, shown in \autoref{fig:countries_network}, are the United States (193 total connections) and China (188 total connections). Besides centrality, the strongest collaboration link is also between the two nations with 53 collaborations. All the most connected countries are signatories of CORSIA. In Europe the biggest nodes are the United Kingdom, Germany and the Netherlands.

