\subsubsection{Titles co-occurence network}
\label{titles_textual_analysis}

Extracted title terms co-occurrence network, in \autoref{fig:titles_network}, reveal the most explored subjects and their relations. It has tree main clusters: in blue the one related to \textbf{alternative fuels} (a.f.) and \textbf{sustainable aviation fuels} (s.a.f.). The presence of the \textbf{review} and \textbf{techno-economic analysis} (tec. acon. analysis) nodes suggest little experimental research on the matter by the papers related to this cluster. The \textbf{life} and \textbf{cycle} terms are certainly related to lyfe cycle assessment (LCA), a technique to quantify the environmental impact of a human activity.

On green, the cluster of more experimental papers, dealing with catalyst research on the conversion of liquid and solid biomass to \textbf{hydrocarbons}. It targets hydrolysis, \textbf{hydroprocessing} and  \textbf{deoxygenation}, to find catalysts highly active on the \textbf{conversion} of biomass, such as \textbf{palm oil}, into hydrocarbons of a suitable range to produce synthetic fuels.

The red cluster is concerned with the \textbf{characteristics} of the fuels produced once the best catalysts and operating parameters are found. These papers characterize the properties of SAF, how it behaves when fed into engines, appropriate blends with current fossil fuels to ease the transition, as well as evaluations of engine \textbf{emissions} and its impacts on \textbf{air} quality.

