\subsubsection{Authors' keywords co-occurence network}
\label{authors_keywords_textual_analysis}

The authors' keywords co-occurrence network in \autoref{fig:authors_keyword_network}, complements the titles analysis, bringing to the front some more useful information. Again, there are three clusters. On the analysis of the viability of biofuels in red one term catches the eye: \textbf{CORSIA} \cite{noauthor_carbon_nodate}. It stands for Carbon Offsetting and Reduction Scheme for International Aviation. A measure by the International Civil Aviation Organization (ICAO) adopted in 2016 to reduce \ce{CO2} emissions from international flights. The objective is to cap emissions at 85\% of what was emitted in 2019 in the period from 2024 to 2035. Furthermore, there is an ambitious commitment to reach zero emissions by 2050 \cite{noauthor_factsheet_2023}. Offsetting involves the use of sustainable aviation fuels, deployment of renewable energy sources, reforestation or any other activity that reduces \ce{CO2} emissions. By 2027, as can be seen in \autoref{fig:CORSIA}, most of the world will be pursuing CORSIA goals. This is a great opportunity for the SAF sector, as airlines will be searching for clean drop-in fuels in order to be able to grow beyond 2019 levels.

